We will soon post a list of independent learning resources on our website, including resources for Target Language Practice. Teachers will also attempt to put this list of resources onto their Google Classrooms. We thank you for your patience and understanding! Please email info@sllis.org if you have any questions.

post_text:
In response to the COVID-19 pandemic, Missouri is offering reimbursements to qualifying families whose children were no longer able to get food from school:

The Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is for families with K-12 children who receive free or reduced-price meals at school, providing up to $302 per eligible child. As of right now, only about 60% of eligible families have taken advantage of this program.

Families receiving SNAP benefits will receive the funds automatically, but other parents must submit a quick application at EmergencyMealSurvey.com/MO before July 7. For additional information, please see the attached flyer or contact Operation Food Search.

post_text: We're very excited to officially announce the opening of SouthSide Early Childhood Center: A Downtown Pre-K Cooperative – an innovative partnership between SouthSide Early Childhood Center and SLLIS, Lafayette Preparatory Academy, and Lift for Life Academy! SouthSide Early Childhood Center is currently seeking teacher candidates to join the dynamic pre-K teaching teams for the classrooms on-site at SLLIS. Please find and share the job postings at https://www.southside-ecc.org/employment-downtown if you or someone you know may be interested!

We remain committed to providing our community with education and resources, and thank all of our stakeholders for your continued support and teamwork.

post_text:
Let's do some Math!
Resting Heart Rate vs. Target Heart Rate:
- Lightly press your index and middle finger on your opposite wrist (below base of the thumb) or lightly press the side of your neck (below the jawbone).
- Count the number of beats for 15 seconds and multiply the result by 4.
- That's your resting heart rate!
Today, we will try to reach our zone 1 ta heart rate (65 to 75%).
- Maximal Heart Rate (MHR) = 220 - AGE.

post_text: On Saturday, Mayor Lyda Krewson announced a mandatory 30 day “Stay at Home” order aimed at preventing further spread of the COVID-19 virus. In light of this new restriction, all schools in the City of St. Louis have decided to extend their closures through April 22. This decision will be continually re-evaluated in coordination with the Mayor’s Office and the City’s Department of Health. The St. Louis Language Immersion School will launch Remote Learning on Monday, March 30, 2020. Please see our website Live Feed and Facebook page for schedules and more details about distance learning.

We are delaying the start of the Spring Session by three weeks. Instead of starting practices this week, we will instead tentatively start practices the week of Monday, April 13. Games will tentatively begin on Saturday, April 18 and final games will tentatively be played Saturday, June 6.

In summary, the tentative Spring Sports Schedule is:

Week of Monday, April 13 – Practices Begin
Saturday, April 18 – First Game
Saturday, June 6 – Final Game
MORE INFO TO COME

shared_text:
Urban Fort Play Cafe
